## Template terms (universal — keep)

| Term | Meaning |
|---|---|
| **Spine** | The 13 standard documentation files in `docs/` (LLM-friendly template). |
| **Generated** | A doc file rebuilt deterministically from source. Has a sentinel `<!-- AUTO-GENERATED -->` comment. |
| **Manual** | A doc file maintained by humans. May receive AI-proposed PRs. |
| **AI** | A doc file (typically only `HISTORY.md`) updated by AI agent passes. |
| **Critical file** | A doc file that always requires human review on changes — never auto-merges. AGENTS.md, ARCHITECTURE.md, OPS.md, SECURITY-NOTES.md, DECISIONS.md (and INFRA.md if present). |
| **Tombstone** | A `<!-- REMOVED ... -->` comment left in a doc file after a section is deleted, preserved for 30 days then swept to `.agents/REMOVALS.md`. |
| **Hash conflict** | When a generated file's current content hash doesn't match what the generator last produced, meaning a human edited it. Triggers a conflict PR. |
| **NO_UPDATE_NEEDED** | The sentinel string an AI step emits when nothing material changed, preventing spurious updates. |

